info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued December 09 at 4:54AM EST until December 09 at 9:00AM EST by NWS Melbourne
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Visibility one half mile or less in dense fog. * WHERE...Northern Lake, Southern Lake, western Orange and northwest Osceola counties. * WHEN...Until 9 AM EST this morning. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Recent surface observations, satellite imagery and traffic cameras show areas of dense fog were reducing visibilities to one half mile or less spreading eastward across Lake county. The fog will continue to develop eastward into western Orange and northwest Osceola counties through sunrise.
info.instruction: If you will be driving early this morning, you may want to plan on leaving early, in order to give yourself plenty of time to safely reach your destination. When driving in dense fog, reduce your speed, use only your low beam headlights, and leave plenty of distance between your vehicle and the one ahead of you.
